messages.content: For Bittensor, can a single consumer request tap into multiple models/peers at the same time - i.e., is there collaboration between the various models for a particular request?  Also, can a model take in the outputs of other models as its own input, and does that lead to the initial model being better than it would've been otherwise (i.e., compared to if it had existed only outside of Bittensor)?  Thank you.

Yes, in fact, that's how the network works: the query goes in through a validator, which passes the query to a subnet of miners, and then returns the best reply (or replies, depending on how the query has been constructed).  I don't believe that the answers that the individual models serve are shared between the models by default; I'm curious to hear from the smarter folks in the room (and specifically, the miners) if anyone has set something up along these lines.

The actual process of fine-tuning -- that is, how each model operator fine-tunes their model(s) -- isn't something that's generally shared (that I know of); I mean, there is general information on what to do, but since Bittensor is competitive, it's not something I would normally see people being eager to share.  But again, if there are smarter/more experienced folks in the room who can talk to this, I would very much appreciate your answers!
